{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5701-fails-javac-compile-com.github.curious-odd-man-rgxgen-3.1-7c1eff7f\n\nThe initial failing stage was `compileTestJava`: `RgxgenTest.java` still used old assertions against `RgxGenOption.getFromProperties(...)`, which returns `Optional<T>` in `3.1`. The concrete compile errors are in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-38-51-445606Z.log` (`isAsciiOnly()` called on `Optional<RgxGenCharsDefinition>`, `containsExactly(...)` on `OptionalAssert<List<WhitespaceChar>>`, and `isTrue()` on `OptionalAssert<Boolean>`).\n\nHowever, the archived reruns show the test fix itself likely worked and the remaining failure is most likely in post-fix preservation/metrics rather than in the library test. `nativeTest` and the full `test` task both pass with 9/9 successful tests in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-39-37-602726Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-40-22-748276Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-40-37-594151Z.log`. The concrete edit is visible in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T11-39-37-593402Z.log`, but the recorded metrics still say `status: failure`, `ending_commit: 2a2429a7...`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None` in `forge/.pending_metrics.json` and `stats/com.github.curious-odd-man/rgxgen/3.1/execution-metrics.json`. The preserved branch currently keeps the logs but not the generated `tests/src/com.github.curious-odd-man/rgxgen/3.1/...` files, so the successful fix was not preserved into branch state.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-38-51-445606Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T11-39-37-593402Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T11-40-37-594151Z.log`\n- `forge/.pending_metrics.json`\n- `stats/com.github.curious-odd-man/rgxgen/3.1/execution-metrics.json`\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Recreate/apply the `RgxgenTest.java` assertion fix from the pi-generation log onto a normal working branch so `tests/src/com.github.curious-odd-man/rgxgen/3.1/...` exists again.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.github.curious-odd-man:rgxgen:3.1` (or at least `compileTestJava` and `nativeTest`) to confirm the passing state already seen in the archived logs.\n3. Investigate why the metrics/preservation step kept `ending_commit` at the starting commit and dropped `test_file`/`metadata_file`, then regenerate/persist the `3.1` stats if needed."}}
